While setting up the build Debug environment I noticed that the TP (at least in my workspace) does not contain the latest o.e.osgi version. After importing the the o.e.osgi project in my PDE-dev workspace the tests also failed when launched from the IDE.

Actually it is obvious that this had to be adjusted as well, but afterwards one is always wiser.
It's great that we had the tests here, they definitely prevented trouble.

Not sure this is usual, especially if Optional is promised in "all cases".

Thomas: WDYT, also in general regarding new API?

Patch Set 6:

> Patch Set 6:
> 
> > Patch Set 6: Code-Review+1
> > 
> > Added explicit throw declaration in javadoc.
> 
> Not sure this is usual, especially if Optional is promised in "all cases".
> 
> Thomas: WDYT, also in general regarding new API?

I would not put a throws NullPointException on the method signature nor in the javadoc.  Generally speaking our API only states if null is allowed.  If the doc does not state null is allowed then it must be assumed null is not allowed and a NullPointException may occur.  That is the way the other methods are specified on Adapters.

I also think it is fine to throw NullPointException here even for a method that returns Optional because it is a programming error to pass null.

Generally the API looks useful.  I question if we will be adding another of method that takes a boolean for allowActivation.

Patch Set 7:

> Patch Set 6:
> I would not put a throws NullPointException on the method signature nor in the javadoc.  Generally speaking our API only states if null is allowed.  If the doc does not state null is allowed then it must be assumed null is not allowed and a NullPointException may occur.  That is the way the other methods are specified on Adapters.

I have adjusted it to not declare the NPE

> I question if we will be adding another of method that takes a boolean for allowActivation.

I think there are very rare cases where this is useful as almost always plugins use eager activation to be activated once they are used. If one then calls allowActivation=false nothing happens and people are confused why their plugin code is not taken into account.
In whole platform code there is just one method actually calling Adapters.adapt method with allowActivation=false and three methods calling it with allowActivation=true.

Beside that, it of course does not make much work to add such method if others think it could be still of value. Just let me know.

From my side this is ready to go.

Patch Set 8: Code-Review+1

LGTM

I agree to avoid another of method to pass a boolean for should activate.  Better to have reduced API than add stuff that no one needs.
